==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Numerator
<hw>Nu"mer*a"tor</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>numerator</ets>: cf. F. <ets>num⟦eacute⟧rateur</ets>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>One who numbers.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Math.)</fld> <def>The term in a fraction which
indicates the number of fractional units that are taken.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ In a vulgar fraction the numerator is written above a
line; thus, in the fraction ⟦frac59⟧ (five ninths) 5 is the numerator;
in a decimal fraction it is the number which follows the decimal point.
See <er>Fraction</er>.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Numerical</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Numeric</ent>⟦br⟧
